      "source": "wikidata"
    },
    {
      "text": "K-1 Revenge, known in Japan as Fighting Illusion: K-1 Revenge (ファイティングイリュージョン 〜K-1 リベンジ〜, Faitingu Iryūjon 〜K-1 Ribenji〜), is a video game based on the K-1 martial arts organization in Hong Kong, developed by Daft and published by Xing Entertainment in Japan in 1997, and by Jaleco in North America in 1999. It is the fifth game in the K-1 Fighting series.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    }
